flavourText: If this is my dream, I don't wish to wake.
Take small pieces of things and then assemble them together
<size:30>{A King Loved By All,
A Shadow Awaiting Nightfall,
A Speaker Howling Away,
A Hunter Seeking Prey}
<size:29>{Come home to me, my sweet.
Oh, how long you've been!
Lie with me in the frozen dark.
I may yet find forgiveness
Now that fear has left you.}
<size:29>{A mind as quick as lightning,
fists as hard as stone,
a heart that burns with fury,
and eyes that chill to the bone.}
If you look hard enough for hidden meaning, you will find it.
<size:30>{"Gaze upon the mirrors of what may come and step backward into infinity."
- Dexion, Thaumetic Aspirant}
True to his title,
Voll, newly crowned,
had many of the
Eternal Empire's signature
extravagances destroyed.
Become the leader you were born to be.
Even the most learned man is a fool to his own fate.
Let these fine arrows pack a punch.
Nothing can be heard above the din or seen amongst the turmoil. The senses are shattered. All is left to fate.
<size:25>{They thought winter had come early,
that snow blanketed the land,
but in truth, all their chickens
had come home to roost.}
"No man can best me, no demon can fell me. For I vanquish all with my axe!"
The jeweller's true talent is the capacity to see a jewel's beauty before they draw it out.
A fond memory fills me with nostalgia; some men would have felt guilt, but I felt no regret over the anguish and fear my ambitions caused.
<size:29>{Moribund, he gazed upon the journey taken as blood trickled down his chin. His eye closed on the city ahead that he would never call home.}
Gaze towards the stars, but beware what gazes back.
The threads of fate are the strongest ties.
The line between having not enough to do and too much to do is unusually fine.
<size:28>{Wreathed in the skin and bones
of the beasts she slew,
her gift came from what she lost:
her humanity.}
<size:32>{Blood flows not just through veins, but through worlds.}
If the path to divinity were simple, we'd all be gods.
One who is blinded by their past may only see a sliver of the present.
"Oh no, I couldn't possibly afford this fine artefact. I'm... just looking."
Feeding on death, they grew stronger and stronger, until they were ready to hatch...
<size:26>{The strange voice showed Aul a future where his legacy was forgotten, where new cultures broke themselves upon Aul's ruined world.}
The Atlas is our prison, and our only defence. She is our only hope, and our certain doom.
"So desperate was I for control, I turned my entire world into a prison. Now you will share in my agony."
<size:28>{You can't seek riches without getting your hands dirty.}
<size:28>{A symbol of beauty and innocence
The gems corrupted her mind
Malachai corrupted her gems
All but a glimmer of
greatness lost in madness}
"When grasped in his hand, even an ordinary piece of wood can make the heavens tremble with fear."
<size:31>{"Daughter of catastrophe, mother of pain. Amongst the filth of Wraeclast, she wanders, and her wrath follows." - Quintoon the Returned}
Claw them from the bottom, you'll be glad that you have got 'em, claw them from the top, you'll never want to stop.
"Many believe murder is a grisly, grim, and grotesque crime. Then there are those who simply make art of it."
It is said anyone who bears this trinket is the luckiest exile in all of Wraeclast. The gods would disagree, and forever curse any whom give it away.
"When they realize our true intent, they will decry us, assault us, and try to crush what we have built. We must stand tall, Qotra, and make the future our own."
Their whims left unknown,
Their life left for others.
"Only after one forsakes rage, can true power be found."
- Sekhema Asenath
<size:30>{Many strive for greatness,
but it is challenge, unforeseen,
that forges heroes.}
<size:26>{"Such dedication for so many years,
all for a couple extra letters at the front of your name..."}
A lucky number
For us all
To help us through
The perils told.
To know the monster, you must become the monster.
"Only a fool looks to the occult for power and expects to be spared from its wrath."
- Voll, Emperor of Purity
The Golden Sekhema's words could solve many a feud. Just what form that solution took was another matter.
<size:29>{"I swore to use my position to help the people. What good is power when it just accumulates on the already-powerful?" - Erasmus, Imperial Gemcutter}
The Mists of Madness prey on those who harbour the deepest of fears.
"How many lives have you consumed?"
"How many times have you blinked?"
"There are two ways to pay, Gold and Blood. I'll take my share in both."
-Cameria the Coldblooded
<size:27>{As Kaom slew the last of his kin,
something deep inside him broke.
And through the cracks, corruption,
pure and black, spread forth.}
In fleeing reality, you step into the realm of madness.
Fall into endless night; a voyage into an ocean of oblivion.
There are countless worlds, but only those with limitless potential will be able to achieve perfection.
<size:31>{"When Voll spared Malachai, accepting his aid in pursuit of Purity, the strongest faith was infected by Corruption and made brittle as glass."
- Victario, the People's Poet}
"Don't worry, I know what I'm doing."
- Toggo's Last Words
No one ever truly understood what she meant when she said she wanted to raise a family.
Sometimes you need to make your own luck.
Upon seeing her face, I am terrifiedâ€”the moon shows me my own form!
I have a headache, can anyone find me a nurse?
Savour these moments, for they may never return.
<size:28>{The mask hides his identity
but also makes it hard to read...}
<size:28>{Charmed by beautiful stones
Consumed with the
pursuit of perfection
Ever deeper into the waiting dark}
"I'm going for a walk. I'll be back soon."
- Blonca's last words
<size:26>{The villain strikes,
the world is torn.
A war begins, a hero is born,
The nemesis sets the sky alight.
A hero's sacrifice
sets everything right.
- Drake's Epitaph}
Though the years weakened his mind, his body remained deadly as ever.
Time cannot wash away that which cannot be forgotten.
To own a piece of the Nightmare, you must first belong to the Nightmare.
Necromancers, believe me, are more terrifying than their thralls.
<size:23>{Vintage or crafted, Glittering and shiny
Dusty or glittering, huge or tiny
Secured within a chest
or unearthed from your mining
Find jewellery everywhere,
no need for divining!
So why is it so hard
to figure out which one to wear?
This one makes me stronger,
but does it match my hair?}
I've never come upon a ship I could not command. I have however met sailors that were not willing to be led.
<size:29>{"Fate was always my nemesis...
But it didn't stop me then, and it won't stop me now."
- Kjetilbrann, The Undaunted}
<size:31>{A wolf does not bite his mate as he does his prey, yet both begin with bared teeth. Know who you are, and you will know the meaning of the bite.}
<size:27>{"There are worlds that lie beyond the edge of my page, the edge of my understanding. Worlds of wonder. Worlds of terror."
Aramil - Cartographer to Emperor Chitus}
Those whose hands are their livelihood know the importance of keeping them safe and warm.
With staff in hand
and wrath in heart,
your soul and corpse
shall surely part.
"There is no right or wrong choice, no best or worst. There are only choices and their consequences."
"Such fine trinkets show their true value in times of crisis." - Tangmazu
In the pursuit of wealth, as in that of power, anything goes.
<size:33>{Weaving through the cracks, searching for weaknesses, silent, indiscriminate, leaving sorrow in its wake.}
Turn the crank,
close your eyes,
and pray to the gods
for a pleasant surprise.
On the 21st of Eterni,
two become one,
their light outshines
the setting sun.
The first quill separates the quick learners from the dead.
An oath once made is an oath never broken. Do not delay in keeping it, for I take no pleasure in fools.
Some things should not be used. Some power is too great a risk.
Be like water, friend.
Some gifts are obligations while others are simply opportunities.
<size:27>{A wanderer in the wild strives
Against countless foes he survives
A fool pursues a quest contrived
By the gift of the witch, alive.}
"Experiment 22A: Rhoas, when deprived of water, secrete a most delightfully potent toxin."
- Maligaro
Sturdy and strong,
grown from the stream.
The Flora that live here,
A combatant's dream.
Two sides of a coin;
Heads for a friend,
tails a foe;
Gemini toss up
<size:30>{"Long ago, people looked to the stars, believing they influenced us. Soon, it will be us who influence the stars."
- Doryani, Queen's Thaumaturge}
Lucian lost himself in ancient scrolls and found in those scrolls a love whose power bridged a millennium.
<size:30>{"I am not alone in this. I have God by my side! And... you help sometimes, I suppose."
- Sister Cassia}
"I don't believe in karma. If it were real, I would never win."
"Sometimes, the most beautiful treasures...are the ones you cannot have."
- Beryl, Survivor from the Azurite Mines
We play at God with our necromancy,
but forces far more potent
sleep within these stones.
Jump right in,
But beware
Of things broken
Or beyond compare.
Unlimited power is apt to corrupt the minds of those who possess it.
Loyalty can be bought. Just make sure you know who the buyer is.
If you beckon the
Lord of Lightning,
do not be surprised
when you are struck.
<size:30>{"Let us not forget the most important lesson the Vaal taught us:
Nothing is eternal."
- Siosa Foaga, Imperial Scholar}
The thumb turns down
and the crowd roars,
they want death
and the blood is yours.
You cannot journey to new lands until you have the courage to leave the safety of home.
The fight is the easy part. It's the years of training that'll kill you.
<size:31>{Publicly, he lived a pious and chaste life of poverty. Privately, tithes and tributes made him and his lascivious company very comfortable indeed.}
They stand among us, and within us.
No matter where your dreams take you, Nightmare follows close behind.
<size:29>{The largest beasts cannot be overpowered. The Greatwolf teaches us to use guile, not strength, to probe for the soft flesh and strike deep.}
Luck is a fool's game, and I know plenty of rich fools.
<size:28>{No blade conquers sin;
guide a sinner to virtue,
unveil their lost sightâ€”
your eyes, too, see in
everyone the inner child,
no matter their might.}
<smaller>{They fought the storm together as one,
Until the longest of days was done.
Their love grew stronger
with every breath,
Until it was broken apart in death.}
You can change your name, but you cannot change your history.
His brother would not atone, so he took his brother's life, and with it, his sins.
A life lost, A legacy born.
By the time their eyes meet,
the dark deal has long since been made,
and his fate long since sealed.
"Hold your tongue before I claim it." - Doedre Darktongue
<size:26>{Embrace death to honour the lost,
no fear in life no matter the cost.
With one of all we are,
and all of one we trust,
throughout past, present and future... be just.}
Though the path to divinity is fraught with peril, hope may bloom from within.
When you dwell in total darkness, even the faintest light may guide you out.
<size:31>{There is no mistake so great that it cannot be undone.}
"Some see our mortal flesh as a limitation. I see it as an opportunity for vast, miraculous improvements."
- Shavronne of Umbra
<size:28>{Scaly beast of the skies,
watching with his golden eyes.
Shadow that blocks out the sun,
it's too late for you to run.}
<size:28>{I never truly understood the depths of my insanity,
until I realized the voices beckoning me towards the abyss,
were none other than my own.}
To her beauty you submit,
lest your neck the great Queen slit.
"Everything I have done has been for Wraeclast. You would pledge your life to me if you saw things my way... and soon, you will."
- High Templar Venarius
Though they were a pack of elite combatants, the Emperor's royal guards were not ready to face one of his notorious parties.
Perfection is the standard, excellence will be handled on a case by case basis.
<size:28>{They gave the stone life. Over eons spent bathed in Corruption, that life evolved.}
Never dying, yet not living,
Endlessly they wander
beneath the harvest moon.
Reach into the Void and claim your prize.
Our Lady Dialla,
as a symbol of our progress,
shines greater than all the gems.
<size:31>{The Eternals lauded his valour. The Karui relished his defeat. Yet the final thoughts of Marceus Lioneye were naught but lament for his pride.}
<size:26>{Black and White, Silver and Gold
Let us see the world Unfold
Red and Blue, Yellow and Green
Let us remake it in colours Unseen}
Wealth can, in fact, buy happiness.
<size:27>{Fire filled the sky that night
Chaos reigned
Where the shards fell
All was destroyed
-Jozen Kasigi, retelling an urban legend of the Cataclysm}
Taste and grow strong. Drink too much and be buried.
In a world filled with chaos, he could always seek comfort in the hands of his master.
From death, life.
From life, death.
The wheel turns,
and the corbies wheel overhead.
It is with the smallest of words that we find the largest of truths.
As countless fractures weaken the divide, nightmares seep through from the other side.

<size:26>{"I wanted to give you three things. I've given you my eternal love. I've sung to you my most beautiful song. I'd have given you the moon last, but it couldn't be found. I hope you'll accept this instead."}
A good spy doesn't forget she's gone undercover.
While the Labyrinth traps have claimed countless adventurers, they were not designed with felines in mind.
Sometimes your greatest enemy is the only one keeping you breathing.
<size:31>{500 times Kaom's axe fell, 500 times Kaom's Heart splintered. Finally, all that remained was a terrible, heartless Fury.}
For a time, we had something stronger than eldritch evil.
We had each other.
<size:28>{First, I gave my wealth, and we went hungry. Next, I gave my land, and we were homeless. Then, I gave my family, and I was alone. Last, I gave my eyes, and all I could dream was mine.}
<size:27>{The mighty warriors traded in blows, the nimble archers in arrows, yet it was the brazen thaumaturgists who would bring catastrophe to all.}
The earth offers nourishment, growth and healing. Unless, of course, the sky has other plans.
You'll never know the things you miss if you keep your eyes closed
Wrapped in the glory of the heavens, she comes to mete out justice for the fallen.
The sun shines not for me. I walk in darkness, never free. Time stopped when you both died in my arms.
"Man may shape the world, but these? These shape the man." -Inquisitor Maligaro
"In the forest again... But at least I have these."
Mold the world with your bare hands. Be careful, for what is your doing might become your undoing.
The house always wins.
Exploring lands made of flesh and sorrow, we'll reap and plunder like there's no tomorrow.
And he shall be heralded by the screams of the damned.
The harvest ended, the floods began.
For every threat you spy in the shadows, there are two others you don't.

<size:25>{"To know for what you fight. To get up again when you've been struck down. To outmanoeuvre someone faster, trick someone smarter, crush someone stronger. That's what it takes to claim the crown."
- Daresso, the King of Swords}
<size:30>{A weapon, a shelter, a prison.
The web's purpose changes
with the spider's needs.
A lesson we should
take to heart.}
Simple actions can lead the world to an early grave.
"Masters of wit, strength and cunning. To survive the harsh winters, you must be like the fox."
- Ezomyte Proverb
<size:28>{"The Seas Call, the Mad Answer"}
<size:30>{Taste not of their
forbidden fruit.
Theirs is a harvest of
the darkest kind,
twisted, rotten and
damned for eternity.}
<size:28>{No man sees all, but you'll see more than some see in a lifetime.}
Life isn't what you make of it, it's already been made for you.
<size:31>{My son, you lost your way before you arrived.
To never lose you again,
I make a path in my heart.}
<size:31>{A month's work, a year's wages, a foolish shortcut through a Rhoa's nest, and a grieving bride-to-be, who never received her betrothed's great gift.}
All dreams vanish when the dreamers wake.
A beacon on the horizon; a guiding light, a call for help, or a warning to turn back.
<size:30>{In a land far away lived
a maiden most fair.
Her smile melted the coldest
of hearts, her song made
men and beast cry,
her beauty unparalleled;
Divine.}
<size:29>{A little extra flair never hurts.}
Scarier than any criminal is an innocent man in chains, for when he breaks free, his revenge will be justified.
To protect her mansion, she would cut a deal with anyone. Anything.
Something answered.
When the world burned, the greedy burned with it, while the clever left as paupers.
The village elders had a curious rule: If you hear three voices scream for aid, flee as fast as you can.
<size:31>{The others succumbed to madness and depravity, but Lori fought on. Alone in the darkness, she could still see the dull light of hope's distant dawn.}
A stereotypical joke may lead to an unexpected bond.
<size:28>{The hatungo know many answers to the same question,
for time itself is a tangled web.}
A map is only useful if you know where you stand.
<size:31>{As their civilisation crumbled, the Vaal looked to their queen. In her, they saw a way out. In them, she saw a burden she was happy to free herself from.}
They say it is the head that leads, but all must flow through the body at some point.
In the hands of a master craftsman, a worthless pebble can adorn the crown of a king.
Eternal beauty has a cost, one which Shavronne was happy to pay with the lives of others.
<size:31>{The end of the old,
the beginning of the new.
A unique opportunity for transformation,
for those with the power
to grasp it.}
Boundless is the distance between where we start and where we start again.
A taste of power brings a hunger for more.
For centuries, they stood vigil in secret over their sleeping goddess, even as contamination oozed out of the decadent Vaal empire.
No man may hope to turn back the storm. You can only hope you do not attract its ire.
The finer the brew, the harder it is to remember drinking it.
When sky meets ground the flames can be found, but who has the will to tame them.
